~ #name: is the single-line form. the colon means "no body".

#year: 1923
#place: Dunmore Head
#keeper: Aldous Vane

~ single-line definitions can still capture and interpolate

#cite: ||author, title, year|| ! ::author:: (::year::). _::title::_. !

~ complex values are wrapped in ! ... ! — may span lines, may contain other nodes

#epigraph: !
The sea does not forgive forgetting.
— coastal proverb
!

#weil: ! Simone Weil, _Gravity and Grace_, 1952 !

~ a #name: definition is used like any other node: @name

He was @keeper. The year was @year.
